 (1962).
Korfhage then joined
the faculty at <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../544/72544.xml">
North Carolina State University</link></university>
 (1962-64), <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../757/23757.xml">
Purdue University</link></university>
 (1964-70),<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref>  <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../109/479109.xml">
Southern Methodist University</link></university>
 (1970-86) and the <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../024/11753024.xml">
University of Pittsburgh School of Information Sciences</link></university>
 (1986-98).  
Korfhages research focused on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../401/12401.xml">
graph theory</link> and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../271/15271.xml">
information retrieval</link>, and he wrote several textbooks and edited several collections in his area.
He died of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../219/105219.xml">
cancer</link> in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../101/25101.xml">
Pittsburgh</link>.  </p>

